Goddard, Pliny - Myths and Tales from the San Carlos Apache, 1918, 88 pages
Goddard, Pliny - Myths and Tales from the White Mountain Apache, 1919, 58 pages
Goddard, Pliny - San Carlos Apache texts, 1919, 228 pages
Goddard, Pliny - White Mountain Apache texts, 1920, 169 pages

The first two books are free translations of the myths, legends, and folklore collected by Goddard during his field work with the Apache in 1910. The second two are word for word translations, and include the original myths in Apache as well as the translations. These were all published in the Anthropological Papers of the American Museum of Natural History in 1920.


